    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is offset by the strong output comparison results (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs) and the direct relevance of the single test condition to the regulatory COU. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support acceptance of the FEA model predictions for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending assessment.",
